<content type="str">Tech Mahindra, a specialist company in digital transformation, consulting and business re-engineering, and Midad Holdings, a part of diversified business conglomerate Al-Fozan Group, has announced the launch of a joint venture, Tech Mahindra Arabia Ltd. The JV company in which Tech Mahindra holds majority stake, would cater to the Saudi Arabian market, a press release issued by Tech Mahindra said. Tech Mahindra Arabia Ltd has also set up a 100-seater delivery center in Al-Khobar and is looking at majorly hiring local talents for the center. A part of the business conglomerate Mahindra &amp; Mahindra, Tech Mahindra has been present in Saudi Arabia since 2006, catering to over 30 active companies in the Kingdom. “The decision to set up a local joint venture company aligns very well with Tech Mahindra’s vision of offering localized technology solutions by building a strong local presence and thus contributing to the local economy,” the press release said. C P Gurnani, CEO and Managing Director, Tech Mahindra, has been quoted as saying, “As a global company, we are driven by the philosophy of ‘think globally and act locally’. Al Fozan Group is a well-respected brand not just in the KSA but in the entire GCC and Middle East. Through our JV with the Group, we will work towards localizing technologies and building local services thus adding value to the local economy.” Headquartered in Al-Khobar, Fozan Group has operations across the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) and Middle East. Abdullah Al-Fozan, Managing Director, Al-Fozan Holding, said, “We are extremely pleased to partner with a well-respected technology brand like Tech Mahindra to launch this JV. As a leading business group in the region, it has been our mission to offer reliable products and services to Saudis and I am sure with this JV, we will be able to offer best-in-breed technology solutions to the enterprises and organizations in the region with the help of a reliable technology brand like Tech Mahindra.” (c) 2017 2016. Alyammamah Press Est. Provided by SyndiGate Media Inc. (Syndigate.info)., source Middle East &amp; North African Newspapers</content> 
